sentences: Margaret Ross Griffel (born 9 July 1943) is an American musicologist and author.
Griffel graduated from High School of Music & Art, in Manhattan, New York in 1961.
She earned a B.A. from Barnard College in 1965, M.A. in European and American History from Boston University in 1966, and a Ph.D. in musicology from Columbia University in 1975.
